The paper deals with the optimization of communication and locomotion in a network of autonomous agents, which involves topics such as control, networking, and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also discusses the use of optimal control theory, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The optimization problem involves communication energy, which is related to networking and information theory, falling under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper applies the framework to a UAV network, which involves robotics and autonomous systems, falling under cs.RO (Robotics).
